---
/** Section 5 — "Agents that grow themselves." The extensibility crescendo:
 *  the self-extension loop as a five-step storyboard, then the pull-quote. */
const steps = [
  { n: '01', title: 'Read', body: 'The agent reads the capsule-authoring guide through the docs tool surface. The docs ship with the OS.' },
  { n: '02', title: 'Write', body: 'It writes a new capsule: a manifest declaring imports, exports, and the capabilities it needs. Nothing more.' },
  { n: '03', title: 'Build', body: 'It compiles the capsule to wasm32-unknown-unknown inside the sandbox. Zero wasi imports; every host call audited.' },
  { n: '04', title: 'Install', body: 'It installs the capsule live. The kernel never restarts and never changes. Capabilities can only narrow.' },
  { n: '05', title: 'Grow', body: 'The OS has a new skill, and the new capsule ships its own docs fragment. The catalog grows. The agent now knows it too.' },
];
---

<section class="grow" id="grow" data-scene>
  <div class="wrap">
    <p class="eyebrow">04 · the point of it all</p>
    <h2 class="grow-title">Agents that <span class="gradient-text">grow themselves</span>.</h2>
    <ol class="grow-steps">
      {
        steps.map((s) => (
          <li class="card grow-step" data-step>
            <p class="mono grow-n">{s.n}</p>
            <h3>{s.title}</h3>
            <p class="dim">{s.body}</p>
          </li>
        ))
      }
    </ol>
    <blockquote class="grow-quote">
      <p>
        “An agent on Astrid can extend itself. It can write a capsule, compile
        it, install it, and call it, all inside the sandbox, all recorded on
        the thread.”
      </p>
      <cite class="mono dim">The Astrid Book, afterword</cite>
    </blockquote>
    <div class="grow-cta">
      <a class="btn" href="/book/capsule-model/designing-capsules/">
        Playground: coming to this tab soon · read the capsule chapters →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .grow {
    padding-block: var(--s-8);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
    background:
      radial-gradient(60% 50% at 50% 0%, color-mix(in srgb, var(--capsule) 7%, transparent), transparent);
  }

  .grow-title {
    font-size: var(--step-5);
    margin-block: var(--s-2) var(--s-6);
    max-width: 16ch;
  }

  .grow-steps {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
    gap: var(--s-2);
    margin-bottom: var(--s-6);
  }

  @media (max-width: 1080px) {
    .grow-steps {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
  }

  @media (max-width: 620px) {
    .grow-steps {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }

  .grow-step {
    padding: var(--s-3);
    display: grid;
    gap: var(--s-1);
    align-content: start;
    transition: border-color var(--t-med) var(--ease-out);
  }

  .grow-step:hover {
    border-color: var(--capsule);
  }

  .grow-n {
    color: var(--capsule);
    font-size: var(--step--1);
  }

  .grow-step h3 {
    font-size: var(--step-1);
  }

  .grow-step .dim {
    font-size: var(--step--1);
    line-height: 1.55;
  }

  .grow-quote {
    max-width: 46rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--s-5);
  }

  .grow-quote p {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--step-2);
    line-height: 1.35;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin-bottom: var(--s-2);
  }

  .grow-quote cite {
    font-style: normal;
    font-size: var(--step--1);
  }
</style>
